definitions.definition: A coupling device consisting of two eyelets or other connection points connected in screw threads . The joint in between can be turned to shorten or lengthen the device with mechanical advantage provided by the screw threads.
A link threaded on both ends of a short bar which is used to pull objects together. (FM 55-501)
The area at either end of a bench where the edge of the glass is padded and meets the boards at a right angle .
examples: A player who is checked into the turnbuckles may be injured.
